==Old Korean==

===Etymology 1===
Most likely from the {{w|Old Chinese}} initial of {{och-l|尸}}. Other, but less likely, hypotheses include that it was a graphic abbreviation of some other character with initial {{IPAfont|*/l/}} (but no such character has been easily identified), or that it was invented in Korea (but there would appear to be no motivation for this, given the commonness of {{IPAfont|/l/}} in all stages of Chinese).

