===Etymology 3===

====Particle====
{{head|oko|particle|tr1=*-lq|tr2=*-q|tr3=*-s}}

# {{non-gloss definition|A genitive case marker chiefly attested after honored animate nouns.}}

=====Usage notes=====
There is a strong argument that {{m|oko||尸}} represents an allomorphic variant of the well-known genitive particle {{m|oko|叱|tr=*-s}} rather than an independent genitive case marker. {{cog|okm|ㅭ|tr=-lq}} and Modern {{cog|ko|ㄹ|tr=-l}} both have the effect of tensing a subsequent consonant. Tensing was also one of the major allomorphs of {{cog|okm|ㅅ|tr=-s}}, see [[ㅅ#Alternative forms]], and is virtually the sole effect of Modern {{cog|ko|ㅅ|tr=-s-}}. Therefore, Old Korean {{m|oko||尸}} was most likely used to denote the tensing effect of {{m|oko|叱|tr=*-s}}.

This notion is further supported by the fact that {{cog|okm|ㅅ|tr=-s}} is the regular reflex of {{m|oko||尸}}. For instance, {{cog|oko|尸中|tr=*qkuy|pos=honorific dative marker}} > {{cog|okm|ᄭᅴ|tr=skuy|pos=id.}} > Modern {{cog|ko|께|pos=id.}}

